        </div>
    </div>
</div>
                        
                        <p>Living artistically at Duke, and anywhere, is not a matter of what we&rsquo;re willing to give up but rather what parts of our identities&mdash;colored flyers and all&mdash;we&rsquo;re willing to contribute to create community. With this understanding, there is no way an arts community at Duke can&rsquo;t, or doesn&rsquo;t, exist. I spent a lot of time here griping about how I couldn&rsquo;t find my own, until I realized &ldquo;my own&rdquo; was, and is, Recess. The essence of art is this type of connection. Really, all you have to do is only connect.</p>

